    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9499" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρήν</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρενός</span>, pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρένες</span>: (1)
          pl., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">midriff, diaphragm</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            10.10</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 16.481</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 9.301</span></i>. Since the word physically
          designates the parts enclosing the heart, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρήν,
            φρένες</span> comes to mean secondarily:—(2) <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">mind,
            thoughts</span>, etc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρεσὶ νοεῖν, κατὰ φρὲνα
            εἰδέναι, μετὰ φρεσὶ βάλλεσθαι, ἐνὶ φρεσὶ γνῶναι</span>, etc.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρένες ἐσθλαί</span>, a good
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">understanding;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρένας βλάπτειν τινί</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.724</span></i>; of the will, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Διὸς ἐτράπετο φρήν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.45</span></i>; feelings, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φρένα
            τέρπετο</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
          1.474</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
